Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the penne.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}(halved).

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}(grated).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} to the pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir in the garlic, @Italian style herbs{1}(stirred in), @tomato puree{30%g} and baby plum tomatoes and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Meanwhile, once the pan of water is boiling, add the @penne pasta{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Add the @water for the sauce{75%ml} and @chicken stock paste{10%g} to the pan with the chicken. Bring to a boil, then turn the heat down and simmer for ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the @baby spinach{100%g} a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once the spinach has wilted, stir through the @creme fraiche{75%g} and half the Cheddar.

Add the cooked pasta and season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then stir to combine.

Share the chicken pasta between your #bowls{} and sprinkle over the remaining Cheddar to finish.

Enjoy!